chunk_content: Use of a unique ID system is recommended. All agencies and IPs serving individuals that meet the definition of OVC_SERV across program models are required to report on 56 this indicator (e.g., OVC partners, DREAMS partners serving AGYW 10-17 years of age with eligible OVC services). Additionally, agencies and IPs implementing approved primary prevention of HIV and sexual violence interventions (e.g., OVC Preventive) are required to report on this indicator regardless P R of funding source. In instances when a Peace Corps Volunteer is placed to work with a CDC, DOD, or E USAID Implementing Partner that provides services to its beneficiaries under the OVC Comprehensive V Model, the Peace Corps support falls under the OVC_SERV Preventive Model. Peace Corps supported E N OVC Activities should be reported according to guidelines outlined in Appendix F. T I Each individual should be counted only once under OVC_SERV in the reporting period.
